==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: ligase
<hw>ligase</hw> <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Biochem.)</fld> <def>An enzyme which
catalyzes creation of a covalent bond between two substrates, resulting
in a larger product which is a combination of the two starting
materials; especially, <stype>DNA ligase</stype>, an enzyme which
creates a phosphate bond between 5⟦prime⟧ and 3⟦prime⟧ ends of a DNA
chain, resulting in a longer chain of DNA. DNA ligase is important in
normal biosynthesis of DNA in the replication cycle of cells.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Ligate</ent>⟦br⟧
